Alpine first appeared on the 1900 U.S. Census as the Alpine Precinct of Apache County. 95 residents in 17 households. It also was recorded  in 1930. In that census it had a white majority.<ref>{{Cite web |year=1930 |title=Population |url=https://www2.census.gov/prod2/decennial/documents/10612963v3p1ch02.pdf |website=Fifteenth Census of the United States |publisher=Bureau of the Census |volume=III, Part I}}</ref> All county precincts were combined into three districts in 1940. Alpine's population was 165 in 1940.<ref>{{Cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZTcjAQAAMAAJ |title=The Attorneys List |publisher=United States Fidelity and Guaranty Company, Attorney List Department |year=1940 |page=85 |language=en}}</ref> The 1960 census estimated 300 persons.<ref>{{Cite encyclopedia |year=1960 |title=Arizona |encyclopedia=World Book Encyclopedia |publisher=Field Enterprises Educational Corporation |location=Chicago |volume=A |page=557}}</ref> In 2010, it was defined as a census-designated place (CDP).

